It’s the end of another love story as Michelle Williams and Chad Johnson have called off their engagement. The former Destiny’s Child singer made the announcement yesterday, December 7 on her Insta-stories. The 38-year-old’s split from the pastor is coming nine months after they got engaged and a month after their reality series “Chad Loves Michelle” premiered. Making the announcement, Williams wrote, “I still remain fearless,” wrote Michelle. “I guess I still remain single! Things didn’t work out. The healing that needs to take place is a must. I don’t wanna destroy another relationship. Blessings to him, his family and his ministry. #Fearless” Williams and Johnson both met in March 2017 at an Arizona spiritual retreat run by Johnson, announced their engagement in April 2018. It would be recalled that earlier this year, Williams sought treatment for mental health.